                            <comment id="13103081" author="nickmbailey" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2011 21:36:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applies to 1.0.0 branch and 0.8 branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103149" author="nickmbailey" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2011 22:45:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Better version of the patch, separate patches for 0.8 and 1.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103151" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2011 22:47:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The question in my mind is, do we want to &quot;unbreak&quot; 0.8.4/0.8.5, and make &quot;endpoints&quot; the same as it was in earlier versions (i.e. listen_address) and add a new field for rpc_address?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103152" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2011 22:49:40 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The question in my mind is, do we want to &quot;unbreak&quot; 0.8.4/0.8.5, and make &quot;endpoints&quot; the same as it was in earlier versions (i.e. listen_address) and add a new field for rpc_address?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I could do it all over again, I wouldn&apos;t have put &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1777&quot; title=&quot;The describe_host API method is misleading in that it returns the interface associated with gossip traffic&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1777&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1777&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in 0.8, but I think at this point changing it back in a minor is bad and will end up causing a lot of confusion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103156" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2011 22:53:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does make it simpler to write a client that works against both latest-0.7 and latest-0.8, though (for 0.8 &amp;gt;= 0.8.6).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Especially if we push 0.8.6 out quickly.  For whatever reason it seems like many 0.8 deployments haven&apos;t moved off of 0.8.1 yet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103159" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2011 22:56:57 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Especially if we push 0.8.6 out quickly. For whatever reason it seems like many 0.8 deployments haven&apos;t moved off of 0.8.1 yet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;True, and now that I think about I&apos;ve heard nothing but complaints about &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1777&quot; title=&quot;The describe_host API method is misleading in that it returns the interface associated with gossip traffic&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1777&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1777&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and no one clamored too hard for it to begin with.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103298" author="nickmbailey" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 03:15:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rebased to make the required parameter listen_address again and add an optional rpc_address.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13103874" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 13 Sep 2011 18:30:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
